accessSwitchSystemCurrentStatus.name: accessSwitchSystemCurrentStatus
accessSwitchSystemCurrentStatus.description: This variable indicates the status of the system. The sysCurrentStatus is a bit map represented as a sum, therefore, it can represent multiple defects simultaneously. The sysNoDefect should be set if and only if no other flag is set. The various bit positions are: 1 sysNoDefect 2 sysOverHeat 3 sysFanRpmLow 4 sysVoltageLow 5 sysThermalSensorFailure

accessSwitchProblemCause.name: accessSwitchProblemCause
accessSwitchProblemCause.description: The variable is the description of sytsem problem.

accessSwitchSystemTemperature.name: accessSwitchSystemTemperature
accessSwitchSystemTemperature.description: The variable is the current temperature in Celsius of the system.

accessSwitchFanRpmEntry.description: A list of rpm information for each fan.

accessSwitchFanRpmCurValue.name: accessSwitchFanRpmCurValue
accessSwitchFanRpmCurValue.description: The current rpm of the fan.

accessSwitchFanRpmMaxValue.name: accessSwitchFanRpmMaxValue
accessSwitchFanRpmMaxValue.description: The maximum rpm ever performed by the fan.

accessSwitchFanRpmMinValue.name: accessSwitchFanRpmMinValue
accessSwitchFanRpmMinValue.description: The minimum rpm ever performed by the fan.

accessSwitchFanRpmLowThresh.name: accessSwitchFanRpmLowThresh

accessSwitchVoltageCurValue.description: The current voltage detected by the sensor (in milli-voltage).

accessSwitchVoltageMaxValue.name: accessSwitchVoltageMaxValue
accessSwitchVoltageMaxValue.description: The maximum voltage ever detected by the sensor (in milli-voltage).

accessSwitchVoltageMinValue.name: accessSwitchVoltageMinValue
accessSwitchVoltageMinValue.description: The minimum voltage ever detected by the sensor (in milli-voltage).

accessSwitchVoltageNominalValue.name: accessSwitchVoltageNominalValue
accessSwitchVoltageNominalValue.description: The nominal voltage which the power should supply (in milli-voltage).

accessSwitchVoltageLowThresh.name: accessSwitchVoltageLowThresh

accessSwitchSysTempEntry.description: A list of temperature information for each sensor.

accessSwitchSysTempCurValue.description: The current temperature detected in Celsius by the sensor.

accessSwitchSysTempMaxValue.name: accessSwitchSysTempMaxValue
accessSwitchSysTempMaxValue.description: The maximum temperature ever detected in Celsius by the sensor.

accessSwitchSysTempMinValue.name: accessSwitchSysTempMinValue
accessSwitchSysTempMinValue.description: The minimum temperature ever detected in Celsius by the sensor.

accessSwitchSysTempHighThresh.name: accessSwitchSysTempHighThresh
accessSwitchSysTempHighThresh.description: The high threshold of the temperature in Celsius. If the current temperature is higher than the threshold, the device will initiate the overheat trap.

accessSwitchMaintenance.name: accessSwitchMaintenance
accessSwitchMaintenance.description: The managed object is for system maintenance. When the EMS wants to trigger the system maitenance operation, the EMS shall send SNMP-SET message to set the corresponding bit value to be 1. The various bit positions are: BIT 1: config save BIT 2: reset BIT 3: local loopback test BIT 4: remote loopback test

accessSwitchMaintenancePort.name: accessSwitchMaintenancePort
accessSwitchMaintenancePort.description: The port which the maintenance operation should be performed on. The value of 0 means the maintenance should be performed on the system.

accessSwitchMaxNumOfStaticVlans.name: accessSwitchMaxNumOfStaticVlans
accessSwitchMaxNumOfStaticVlans.description: The maximum number of static VLANs which the system supports

acccessSwitchChassisId.name: acccessSwitchChassisId
acccessSwitchChassisId.description: The chassis Id of the module

accessSwitchSlotId.name: accessSwitchSlotId
accessSwitchSlotId.description: The slot Id of the module

accessSwitchFWVersion.name: accessSwitchFWVersion
accessSwitchFWVersion.description: The firmware version of the access switch.

accessSwitchDriverVersion.name: accessSwitchDriverVersion
accessSwitchDriverVersion.description: The driver version of the access port in this access switch

accessSwitchModemCodeVersion.name: accessSwitchModemCodeVersion
accessSwitchModemCodeVersion.description: The modem code version of the access port in this access switch

accessSwitchDSLConfOps.name: accessSwitchDSLConfOps
accessSwitchDSLConfOps.description: The managed object is for xDSL line configuration. When the EMS wants to issue the desired operation, the EMS shall send SNMP-SET message to set the corresponding bit value to be 1. The various bit positions are: BIT 1: enable port BIT 2: disable port BIT 3: set DSL mode BIT 4: set profile

accessSwitchDSLConfTarget.name: accessSwitchDSLConfTarget
accessSwitchDSLConfTarget.description: The managed object is used for identify the target on which the line configuration should be performed. The target is encoded as: Byte 1~4: reserved Byte 5~7: each octet specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, etc. Byte 8~10: reserved

accessSwitchDSLConfMode.name: accessSwitchDSLConfMode
accessSwitchDSLConfMode.description: The DSL mode. The semantic for each bit is: Bit 1: ADSL, G.lite Bit 2: ADSL, G.dmt Bit 3: ADSL, T1.413 Bit 4: ADSL, Auto

asDot1xPortTable.description: This table includes the configuration of 802.1x.

asDot1xPortControl.description: The configuration defines the 802.1x port control type.

asDot1xPortReAuthPeriod.description: The configuration defines the 802.1x re-authentication period for each port.

asMacDisplayTarget.name: asMacDisplayTarget
asMacDisplayTarget.description: This managed object is a filter used for identify the target from which the MAC addresses are learned in macTable. The target should be IfIndex which is used for identifying subscriber ports (e.g. 300 means all ports in slot 3 and 301 means port 1 in slot 3).

asMacTable.name: asMacTable
asMacTable.description: A table that contains information about unicast entries for which the bridge has forwarding and/or filtering information. This information is used by the transparent bridging function in determining how to propagate a received frame.

asMacAddress.name: asMacAddress
asMacAddress.description: A unicast MAC address for which the bridge has forwarding and/or filtering information.

asMacPort.name: asMacPort
asMacPort.description: The port from which the mac address has been learned.

reboot.name: reboot
reboot.description: Send a message to the manager that the system is going to reboot. The variable is the reason why the system reboots.

systemShutdown.name: systemShutdown
systemShutdown.description: Send a message to the manager that the system is going to shutdown. The variable is the reason that causes the system to shutdown.

overheat.name: overheat
overheat.description: Send a message to the manager that the system is overheated. The variable in the binding list is the current temperature in Celsius of the system.

overheatOver.name: overheatOver
overheatOver.description: Send a message to the manager that the overheated condition is over. The variable in the binding list is the current temperature in Celsius of the system.

errLog.name: errLog
errLog.description: Send a message to the manager that an error log is created in system. The variable in the binding list is the content of the error log.

fanRpmLow.name: fanRpmLow
fanRpmLow.description: Send a message to the manager that the rpm of the fan is too low. The variable in the binding list is the current rpm of the fan.

fanRpmNormal.name: fanRpmNormal
fanRpmNormal.description: Send a message to the manager that the low-rpm condition of the fan is over. The variable in the binding list is the current rpm of the fan.

voltageOutOfRange.name: voltageOutOfRange
voltageOutOfRange.description: Send a message to the manager that the voltage of the system is out of range. The variable in the binding list is the current voltage in volt of the system.

voltageNormal.name: voltageNormal
voltageNormal.description: Send a message to the manager that the low-voltage condition is over. The variable in the binding list is the current voltage in volt of the system.

systemMaintenanceFailure.name: systemMaintenanceFailure
systemMaintenanceFailure.description: Send a message to the manager that the system maintence operation fail. The variable in the variable binding indicates the problem.

configChange.name: configChange
configChange.description: Send a message to the manager that the system configuration data is changed.

thermalSensorFailure.name: thermalSensorFailure
thermalSensorFailure.description: The trap signifies that the thermal sensor failed.
